===Etymology===
From the {{der|en|sla}} suffix represented by {{cog|ru|-ник}}. This suffix experienced a surge in English coinages for nicknames and diminutives after the 1957 Soviet launch of the first [[w:Sputnik program|Sputnik satellite]]. English usage is heavily influenced by {{der|en|yi|-}} usage of {{m|yi|־ניק}} and similar borrowed words ([[nogoodnik]], [[nudnik]], [[kibbutznik]]).

